            %p You can turn any link into a trigger for a modal, simply by setting the data-action attribute of the link to "modal". You can then either set the href to a section of content hidden on the page, or load something remotely with AJAX by setting the data-url property of the link.
            %a.btn{"data-action" => "modal", :href => "#some_content"} Load Local Content
            %a.btn{:data => {:action => "modal", :url => "ajax.html"}, :href => "#"} Load Remote Content
            #some_content.hidden
              %h2 This is modal content!
              %p
                Modals can load content hidden on the page or load content through AJAX by giving the link a data-url attribute with the url of the content you want to load.
